default The Local Government Technical Advisers Group 
default(
defaultTAG
default)
default represents a large number of local authorities in the country, these include those with highway and transport responsibilities; such as Transport for London, most London boroughs, Metropolitan authoritie
defaults, Unitary authorities
default, consultants providing highway and transport services for major local authorities and
default many of the districts an
defaultd towns in two tier authorities. 
defaultWhile these ‘second tier’ authorities do not have direct responsibility for transport, 
defaultthey do have a major role in looking after significant towns and the sensible overall planning of them including providing a reasonable environment and trying to ensure
default,
default through the Highways and Transport Authorities
default,
default that the transport system is fit for p
defaulturpose. 
defaultOverall we represent over 100 different authorities.
default Thus for any technical or professional group, we believe we are the most effective representative organisation likely to have a technical as well as public view on any policy issues
