defaultSummary, linksdefault and published reports on road building induced traffic and congestiondefaultThere is
default very strong 
defaultevidence 
default(but not as widely known as it should be) 
defaultthat road building can increase traffic levels enormously; although the mechanisms – mode change, redistribution,
default peak narrowing, genuine new trips etc 
default&#xa0;
defaultresulting in the extra traffic is less clear.
defaultCongestion at the end of the new roads and elsewhere from the extra traffic
default,
default 
defaultalthough very visible, 
defaultis much harder to quantify properly.
